Also - I paused a test and now it says I failed and I cannot come back.  And to make matters worse - the failed test makes the course uncompleted so I might not get my certificate.  VERY FRUSTRATING.  There are way better FRB advertising courses out there

It was very difficult to stay focused or interested in this course.  I found the speaker to sound somewhat monotone, and at times difficult to understand. Some words were said so quickly, the other times there were strange pauses where there shouldn't be one. I also read the text after every video to help me as I've learned though all the courses, and I noticed even the text didn't make sense in this course. There were periods in the middle of sentences, then others were run on sentences, and words replaced with other words because the captioning system couldn't even properly understand.  This made the course very difficult to follow along with and learn from. I also found it to be poorly organized. As an example, the word "Pixel" was introduced to us and the instructor said we would discuss that at a later time. Then the word was continuously used through multiple videos while we still had not been taught what it meant. It's difficult to follow when you have not even learned the vocabulary being used in the lesson.

The course is well presented and built, but it is not updated with the latest Facebook modifications, and this is not ok. I am paying to learn how to advertise on Meta / Facebook and all, and I am taking quizes, but I am learning something that is different from reality. Of course I will check on the Meta website & support and learn the new updates separate from the course, but it is not ok. I thought you guys have a live contract with Meta and you are selling updated stuff due to that contract. Whatever... I am happy I learned and got my certificate, but I am also very dissappointed, because what I learned must be completed somewhere else, though I paid for updated information.
Not much information that I could use outside of what I already know. Was wanting a refresher course and it was a whole bunch of introduction videos

I found this course to be the most challenging one of the six Facebook Social Media Marketing series. As it is the most theoretical one, it is expected to be challenging. However there are two things, that made the learning experience harder. First of all I wish Anke Audenaert would be the tutor on this course as well, as she is naturally a good speaker and makes the learning experience more pleasant. Some people are naturally talented when it comes to using their voice and presenting. Or another option would be having a native English speaker to present this course, as it was very tiring to follow up the commentary. Not watching the videos and only following the content from the text is not an option, as this is visual experience. So the presenter could have been chosen respecting these issues. The second challenge was the structure of this highly theoretical content. For people who are not familiar with the Ads Manager, I think it would be easier to understand, if the course started by creating and actual campaign and then started to break down the components of Ads Manager accordingly. If "ampaign Creation in Ads Manager Walk Through" from Week 5 would be the first lesson on Week 1, I feel that I would get a better picture and I would be more engaged from the start.

The course was very informative. There was no focus on A/B testing and how those features within facebook ads manager work.  I was hoping to learn more about how I move on with what I learn from my new ads and audiences. For example - I've completed a new campaign and developed a custom audience. Now I have the results. Where to go from there? Sure we covered what some of the results might mean for certain ads. How do I continue to retarget and hone in on my audiences. That was not covered from what I understood.
Too much theory, too little practical knowledge.
